Have you ever shared your goals and dreams with someone, only to have them tell you that it's impossible? 

My friend, I have been there and let me tell you it can be a huge blow to your confidence and motivation. 

But here's the truth: your goals are not impossible.

The only thing that can make them impossible is if you let others' doubts and negativity weigh you down. 

It is crucial to surround yourself with people who believe in you and support you no matter what. You need people who breathe life into you and inspire you to keep going, even when things get tough.

So, take a moment to evaluate the people in your life. 

Are they pushing you to be your best self, or are they dragging you down with their doubts and negativity? 

Remember, you are capable of achieving your goals and making your dreams a reality. 

Don't let anyone else tell you otherwise.

DO YOU WANT TO BUILD A STRONG FAMILY AND BUSINESS AT THE SAME TIME?

Here are 3 tips that will help you build a strong family and business:

1 MAKE YOUR FAMILY A PRIORITY.

If your family isn't included in your calendar, that's a big problem. You get what you schedule. Don't schedule work, hobbies, fitness, etc and hope you find time for your family.

Schedule in your date night. Schedule in time at the park.

Schedule in time for family dinner. We don't lack time, we lack priorities

2 ENLIST YOUR FAMILY IN YOUR BUSINESS.

Discuss your business goals with your family & create rewards for achieving them. Enlisting your family will help them go from resentful to supportive of your work. 

Make the shift from "your goals" to the "family goals". You'll be surprised how active they will be on helping you hit them.

They want to be a part of your business.

3 CONNECT THROUGH COMMUNICATION.

Communication helps close gaps in expectations. You become more connected through frequent communication.

Drop the word "FAMILY" if you're determined to build a strong family and business at the same time.

You DON'T have to have all the ANSWERS to SUCCEED

Have you ever had it when someone asks you a question, but you don't know the answer to it?

How do you succeed when you are new and don't know the answer? 

Here's how:

1 BE HONEST ABOUT IT

Don't pretend like you know the answer. 

People know you don't know. 

Just simple say, "I don't know."

2 FIND OUT THE ANSWER FOR THEM

After telling them, "I don't know", follow up with, "But, I will find out."

People will admire you for your honesty and willingness to help them find out the answer for them.

3 TELL THEM WHAT YOU KNOW INSTEAD

Now, stand strong. Tell them what you do know. Simply say, "But what I do know is”

By using this phrase, you're showing them that there are more things you know.

Remember, it's better to be honest than to pretend you know something because, in the end, people will know it if you're lying.

I was asked the question, “How do you have confidence when you are just beginning?” 

There are a lot of things that affect our confidence. Here are a few: 

Your experience
Your posture
The way you dress
The way you show up on time
The way you prepare

Here’s a secret for you: Borrow other people’s confidence while building your own. 

People can lend you their confidence while you’re building your own. This will help you gain confidence others can also use to develop their own. 

Sir Isaac Newton mentioned before, “If I have seen further, it is by standing upon the shoulders of giants.” 

This implies that we can also borrow vision from the vision of all the great people we surround ourselves with. 

Become a great storyteller, and borrow the confidence, posture, credibility, and strength of people you work with until you’ve earned enough to own your own story. 

Drop the word “CONFIDENCE” if you’re not afraid to lend other people’s confidence until you’ve built your own.
